Whoo hoo!!!

The 2020 Panorama yearbook will be delivered to homes Thursday, July 30th!

The yearbook was sold out but our publisher printed a small number of additional copies! You can order one of the last copies at yearbookordercenter.com and we are order number 4429. The online sale will end on Tuesday the 28th or when the additional copies are sold out!

Once again, a happy group of delivery people will be dropping off the Panorama yearbook Thursday, July 30th! Thank you all for your patience, as the publisher was way behind schedule due to the shutdown!

post_text:
Important Announcement Regarding the 2020 Panorama Yearbook!

We have received word from our publisher that unfortunately the 2020 Panorama delivery date will be delayed. Our book is scheduled to ship on August 1st.

The yearbook is submitted and printed in increments throughout the year. Due to the Covid 19 virus the printing process was halted for several weeks. The plant is now printing books again but due to social distance guidelines they have to work with a much smaller staff. Our publisher has always been very reliable but they are overwhelmed with thousands of books to print and ship and are understaffed.

We apologize for the delay. We are planning on delivering the yearbooks as soon as the books arrive. We will announce when the books have arrived and when to expect them.

Thank you for your patience.

Panama Central School District is with Kay Kiser Jackson and 9 others.
June 4, 2019 at 8:40 AM ·

Some of the graduating class of 2019 looped with Mrs. Sard in 1st and 2nd grade. During those two years, the students and Mrs. Sard created a lasting bond.

At the end of their time together, Mrs. Sard was presented with a photo of her students that she has kept on display all these years.

Before they graduated, the seniors decided to recreate the photo and give it to Mrs. Sard this morning. Take a look!

Thank you to these seniors for making this happen! These are the moments that make Panama so amazing.

November 3, 2017 at 10:03 PM · Buffalo, NY ·

Proud mom tonight! Not just of my own girls, but of my swim girls too :) Karianne Yuchnitz won the 50 Free tonight - the first PCS swimmer to win a Sectional swimming event! And she placed 4th in the 100 Free! Izzi competed in the 200 and 500 and the 200 Free Relay (Abi Bailey, Isabel Bailey, Leah Saxton and Karianne Yuchnitz) broke the school record! Izzi, Karianne, Leah and Lauren Barmore competed in the 400 Free Relay! A great night of swimming! Proud and thankful to be a Panther!!

Panama Elementary is currently in 2nd place in WKBW's Weather Machine contest. We would like to have Andy Parker bring his Weather Machine to our school for a cool Weather assembly. But we need your help! We have five more days of voting to try to take over 1st place. We need the help of our entire school community!! Andy said it is usually the parent and community votes that make the difference! You can find a link to voting on the PCS homepage. You can vote as often as you would like to throughout the day. We are battling with Blasdell Elementary for the first place spot.

Today's word (Wednesday) is FOG. Look each day at the PCS homepage for the word of the day. Spread the word to friends to help us increase our vote total.

Panama Elementary is currently in 2nd place in WKBW's Weather Machine contest. We would like to have Andy Parker bring his Weather Machine to our school for a cool Weather assembly. But we need your help! We have five more days of voting to try to take over 1st place. We need the help of our entire school community!! Andy said it is usually the parent and community votes that make the difference! You can find a link to voting on the PCS homepage. You can vote as often as you would like to throughout the day. We are battling with Blasdell Elementary for the first place spot.

Today's word (Wednesday) is FOG. Look each day at the PCS homepage for the word of the day. Spread the word to friends to help us increase our vote total.

Attention Panama Players!

Auditions for the musical start next Monday, December 4th! Auditions are not to see whether or not you make it in. If you are in 7th-12th, we want you to be a part of this year's production, Shrek The Musical! Auditions are for you to get a chance to experience being on stage and for the directors to get an idea of who would be best for each role. So, please, sign up to audition! Sign ups and audition information and materials are in the music wing outside of Mr. Johnson's room.
